A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Donald J. Trump; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Donald J. Trump was re-elected on November 5, 2024, winning the electoral
3 and popular vote, as the 47th President of the United States, the second candidate in
4 American history to be elected to the office in two non-consecutive terms, gaining the
5 confidence of millions of American voters; and
6 WHEREAS, President Trump has appointed and nominated a record number of women,
7 minorities, and individuals from a wide range of backgrounds to key leadership positions,
8 including appointing the first female White House Chief of Staff and youngest White House
9 Press Secretary in history; and
10 WHEREAS, President Trump has made several key commitments in line with his America
11 First agenda, to include sealing the United States border, keeping our communities safe,
12 ending high inflation, extending American worker tax cuts, and establishing America as a
13 dominant energy producer in the world; and
