14 WHEREAS, in his first term, his pro-growth, pro-worker economic policies fueled
15 unprecedented GDP growth, lower taxes for individuals and businesses, affordable prices for
16 consumers, and technological innovation whilst eliminating burdensome regulations; and
17 WHEREAS, he led the United States into energy independence for the first time in decades
18 with initiatives such as opening federal lands to oil and gas exploration, approving the
19 Keystone XL and Dakota Access pipelines, and ending undue reliance on foreign energy
20 sources; and
21 WHEREAS, President Trump appointed over 200 federal judges, including 54 federal
22 appellate judges and three Supreme Court justices—Neil Gorsuch, Brett Kavanaugh, and
23 Amy Coney Barrett—whose decisions will shape the legal landscape for generations; today,
24 more than a quarter of active federal court judges are Trump appointees; and
25 WHEREAS, he adopted a "peace through strength" approach to foreign policy to restore
26 international American leadership, hold our adversaries accountable at the United Nations,
27 and bring peace to the Middle East through the Abraham Accords; and
28 WHEREAS, President Trump has demonstrated an unwavering commitment to restoring
29 American sovereignty and ending the abuse of our immigration system by implementing the
30 "Remain in Mexico" policy, constructing over 450 miles of new border wall, and cracking
31 down on illegal sanctuary cities.
32 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
33 commend the 45th and 47th President of the United States Donald J. Trump for his
34 re-election and successful conservative policies as well as extend their best wishes for his
35 continued leadership.
